    "summary": "pcs security update",
    "details": "\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA vulnerability was found in the PCS project. This issue occurs due to incorrect permissions on a Unix socket used for internal communication between PCS daemons. A privilege escalation could happen by obtaining an authentication token for a hacluster user. With the \u0026quot;hacluster\u0026quot; token, this flaw allows an attacker to have complete control over the cluster managed by PCS.(CVE-2022-2735)",
